    "aonid": 4020,
    "game-obj": "Equipment",
    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "Your very quintessence has been hijacked by the agony of Dahak that lingered within your bound dragon. The wracked god\u2019s whispers burn your soul and ride your body to work in dire concordance with his whims. You are the very face of horror, an heir of the Dragon Plague\u2019s rancor, the Endless Destruction made manifest in an overwhelmed mortal form. You gain the Scream of Unending Destruction activity. In exchange, the dragon who bound you to this pact is now free from the influences of Dahak, losing any boons or abilities that might have been granted if they were a follower of Dahak and gaining a +2 item bonus on saving throws against any spells or abilities cast by followers of Dahak.",
        "sections": [
            {
                "name": "Oathbreaker's Calamity",
                "type": "section",
                "text": "The souls of both parties begin to become consumed by the agony of Dahak. At the end of each day, you and your dragon become doomed 1 (or increase your doomed values by 1 if you\u2019re already doomed) unless both of you acted in service to Dahak that day. If you or your bound dragon die while under this effect, both of you explode in a catastrophe of hellfire and pitch, dealing 16d6 fire damage to all creatures in a 30-foot emanation; this effect has the divine and unholy traits. If the creature who didn\u2019t die also survives this blast, the pact of the agonized destroyer ends.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "doomed",
                        "alt": "doomed",
                        "game-obj": "Conditions",
                        "aonid": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "emanation",
                        "alt": "emanation",
                        "game-obj": "Rules",
                        "aonid": 2387
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "divine",
                        "alt": "divine",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 579
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "unholy",
                        "alt": "unholy",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 521
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
        "level": 18,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Rare",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 137,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
                "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "rare"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Contract",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "legacy",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Legends",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Legends pg. 10",
                            "alt": "Legends pg. 10",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 40
                        },
                        "page": 10
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "9b1412649bade212276b4bc5db25d991",
                "text": "A contract is a type of item that magically establishes an agreement between multiple parties and typically grants magical benefits.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Invested",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 98,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "GM Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core pg. 219",
                            "alt": "GM Core pg. 219",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        },
                        "page": 219,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "56b56ea5f9d865dc549f0ed7372ab504",
                "text": "A character can invest only 10 magical items that have the invested trait. None of the magical effects of the item apply if the character hasn\u2019t invested it, nor can it be activated, though the character still gains any normal benefits from wearing the physical item (like a hat keeping rain off their head).",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "invest",
                        "alt": "invest",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2799
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Magical",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 103,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 458,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
                "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            }
        ],
